Setting the state has a first argument which is the previous state.

For [async operations](https://reactjs.org/docs/state-and-lifecycle.html#state-updates-may-be-asynchronous), you need to make use of the previous state.

```
setNewState((previousState) =&gt; ({
  ...previousState,
  key: &#39;newValue&#39;,
}));
```

In here, `oldState` is != `previousState`.

